Fabrication of "Korea-Japan Annexation Treaty" Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The Japanese imperialists are a fraud of international laws and a shamelessly heinous robber as they fabricated "Korea-Japan Annexation Treaty" and enforced unheard-of harsh colonial rule over Korea for over 40 years.
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed article Tuesday, 95 years after the fabrication of the treaty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The treaty was illegal and false from A to Z as the Japanese imperialists cooked it by force after occupying Korea and it was "concluded" in a coercive and conspiratorial way in defiance of the general requirement and procedures for a treaty, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that any treaty bearing the false ratification of the top ruler of a country, the most important precondition for its effectuation, has no legal binding force. However, the Japanese imperialists forged the ratification of the Korean king for the above-said treaty in gross breach of international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "annexation treaty" has already been recognized as illegal one by the United Nations, and the Japanese imperialists, too, had no way but to admit that the treaty had no legality and validity. This can be proved by the fact that they kept the fabricated treaty as a top secret and announced it to the world on August 29, one week after its concoction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reactionaries of Japan are now claiming that the annexation of Korea by Japan was "lawful" and the Korean people "benefited" from Japan's colonial rule although it committed such hideous crime of violating international law. This illogical assertion is an intolerable insult and a mockery of the Korean people.
 It is the will of the Koreans to certainly force Japan, their sworn enemy, to pay for its past crimes no matter how much water may flow under the bridge and how many times generations are replaced, the article says, urging Japan to settle its crime-woven past as early as possible.

Furnace Firing Ceremony Held at Taean Friendship Glass Factory 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- A furnace firing ceremony was held Monday at the Taean Friendship Glass Factory now close to its completion.
 Present at the ceremony were Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Pak Pong Ju, Minister of Construction and Building-Materials Industries Tong Jong Ho, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kim Yong Il, Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade Ri Ryong Nam, officials concerned, officials and workers, builders and soldier-builders of the glass factory.
 Also present there were members of the Chinese government economic and trade delegation led by Chen Jian, assistant to the minister of Commerce, Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, and staff members of the embassy here, Teng Fuquan, general director of the Yaohua Glass Group Corporation of China, and other Chinese technicians, workers and guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryang Jang Gyun, vice-minister of Construction and Building-Materials Industries, in his speech said that the construction of the Taean Friendship Glass Factory now making successful progress under the deep care of the top leaders of the DPRK and China will greatly inspire the Korean people in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the Korean people would as ever join the fraternal Chinese people in making every possible effort to boost the traditional friendship between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chen Jian, assistant to the minister of Commerce, noted that the furnace of the factory has been fired to provide a guarantee for the successful commissioning ceremony thanks to the concerted efforts of the governments and builders of the two countries.
 He hoped that the Chinese and Korean technicians and workers would closely cooperate with each other and wind up all the preparations for the commissioning of the factory in time and in good quality, true to the expectation of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The participants in the ceremony broke into an enthusiastic applause when Ryang Jang Gyun and General Officer of the Korean People's Army Ri Song On and Chen Jian and Wu Donghe pressed the buttons to start a fire in the furnace respectively on behalf of the DPRK side and the Chinese side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Firecrackers were set off and brass band music resounded forth outside the furnace shop. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants went round the furnace and other main production processes.

Vigorous Movement for Independent Reunification Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The August 15 grand festival for national reunification was successfully held and multi-faceted dialogues and contacts, cooperation and exchanges are brisk between the north and the south of Korea. This is a positive and encouraging development which proves that no desperate efforts on the part of the reactionaries at home and abroad can block the process of reconciliation, peace and independent reunification in the Korean Peninsula and the movement for achieving independent reunification in the spirit of "By our nation itself" is sure to triumph.
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint slogans made public by the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea on the occasion of the 60th anniversary of the WPK call upon all the Korean people to achieve fresh successes and greater progress in the present struggle for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is, indeed, painful that the Korean nation has not yet achieved the country's reunification though 60 years have passed since its division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The national division that persists even in this new century has brought untold misfortune and pain to all Koreans, hindering the uniform development of the nation.
 It is a solemn call of history and an urgent demand of the times to bring about a fresh surge in the movement for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now is the time to more dynamically push ahead with the movement for national reunification on a new stage of development and bring about a landmark phase for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was a very timely and patriotic step that the joint slogans called for opening a landmark phase for independent reunification in this significant year.
 It is necessary to hold fast to the principle of national reunification and thoroughly implement the tasks laid down by the joint slogans. Doing so is a shortcut to advancing the movement for independent reunification to steady victory. 
The Korean nation's will for independent reunification is strong and their fighting spirit is sky-high. No force on earth can stand in the way of the Korean nation as it is equipped with the conscience of national independence and strong will for independent reunification.

Anniv. of Kim Jong Il's Visit to Far Eastern Region of Russia Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Tuesday dedicates a signed article to the third anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's visit to the Far Eastern region of Russia.
 The article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His visit to the Far Eastern region of Russia marked an immortal epical event to be conveyed to posterity along with the advance of history as it is brilliantly recorded in the annals of the DPRK-Russia friendship &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His visit to the region opened a favorable phase for guaranteeing peace and stability in Asia and the rest of the world and building a new just world structure.
 The immortal exploits he performed by conducting his external activities in the days of his tour of the above-said region have given a powerful impetus to the development of the friendly and cooperative relations between the two peoples and the movement for global independence with great vitality and magnetic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Russia friendship has developed in various aspects to meet the desire and interests of the two peoples under the special care of the top leaders of the two countries. Personal letters and messages of greetings have been exchanged between the top leaders on different occasions and the exchange of delegations including high-level ones has become brisk. The two countries have taken common approaches towards the issues of bilateral state security and major issues related to international relations. They have made efforts to ensure peace and stability in Northeast Asia and the rest of the world and establish a new fair international order. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian people have registered successes in their efforts to achieve the political stability and unity of the country and build powerful Russia under the leadership of President Putin. The Korean people are following with keen interest the positive changes taking place in Russia and appreciating the successes made by the people in their efforts to build powerful Russia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are working hard to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, true to the Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new turning phase is being brought about in the efforts of the Korean people to achieve national reunification under his tested leadership. The Russian people have expressed sympathy and support for the Korean people in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful nation of Juche and achieve peace and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It is in full line with the desire and interests of the two peoples to steadily boost the DPRK-Russia friendship. And it is the consistent stand of the DPRK to give a steady continuity to the history of the traditional DPRK-Russia friendship, the article concludes.

Zambian Government Delegation Arrives
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- A government delegation of the Republic of Zambia led by Vice-President Lupando Mwape arrived here today.
 It was greeted at the airport by Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Hyong Jun, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Ri Myong San, vice-minister of Foreign Trade, Kim Yong Suk, vice-minister of Agriculture, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A welcome function took place at the airport. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the playing of the national anthems of Zambia and the DPRK, Lupando Mwape reviewed with Yang Hyong Sop a guard of honor of the Korean People's Army.

1/f Fluctuation Treatment System
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- The newly developed 1/f fluctuation treatment system has proved successful in clinical practice in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. It, developed by the Medical Appliances Institute under the Academy of Medical Science, was highly appreciated at the 8th national show of scientific and technical successes gained in the public health sector held from August 1 to 10.
 The computer-aided system, the third generation of body-stimulating treatment system, is based on the principle of 1/f fluctuation common to the natural world and the living body. It controls labor pain and homeostasis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 1/f fluctuation system with sound effects of famous songs gives impetus to the part of disease and thus treats patients while they feel pleasant and comfortable.
 The system is applicable to the treatment of various kinds of neuralgia including brachialgia, sciatica and backache, insomnia, autonomic imbalance, hypertension, stress, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has no side effect in comparison with the existing electro puncture appliances and physiotherapist appliances using direct current and low frequency, high frequency, ultrasonic waves and microwave. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Years of clinical test over some 1,000 patients show that 80 percent of them have recovered their health from insomnia, autonomic imbalance, hypertension, brachialgia, sciatica, backache and other diseases.

Livestock Co-op Farms for Pyongyang
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, August 23 (KCNA) -- There are five livestock farms (Kubin, Ransan, Songsok, Thaejam and Munhwa) in Kangdong County, Pyongyang, the
Democratic People��s Republic of Korea.
 They have more than 10,000 superior breeding goats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Kubin farm is raising nearly 2,000 goats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The other four farms are pasturing several thousand goats in their natural and artificial grass fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Each household of the farms raises 3-5 goats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The farms have built well-furnished fodder production and milk-processing workshops and are turning out large quantities of processed milk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They provide processed milk including kefir and goat meat to over 20 kefir service centers and branches and foodstuff shops in the city.
